author: David Kelly
title: Cardinals Gameday: Ravens
text:
Cardinals Gameday: Ravens - Tucson News Now Member Center: dkelly@tucsonnewsnow.com 
Joe Flacco and the Baltimore Ravens (1-5) are about to enter some dangerous air space. 
The AFC North team comes into University of Phoenix Stadium Monday night to face the best team in the NFL in stealing the football by air. 
The Arizona Cardinals (4-2) lead the league in interceptions with 11. The Birds have returned three of those interceptions for touchdowns. 
As a result of their penchant for taking opponentâ€™s passes out of the air, the Cardinals secondary has been dubbed the No Fly Zone. 
Kickoff of Monday Night Football is 5:37 p.m. 
Our Dave Cooney will be in Glendale with reports tonight on KOLD News 13 and on FOX 11 Tucson.
